author: dkulp
msg: Tag things before merging the maven2/refactoring stuff in case something is really screwed up we can go back easily.

author: dkulp
msg: * Move most of configuration base classes to celtix-common
* Create beangen maven plugin and get rid of remaining antrun stuff for codegen
* Move generated spring config items to celtix-api and get rid of celtix-configtypes
* Fix a LOT of XML handling/parsing to use InputSource with proper systemId set instead of InputStream so relative paths can be resolved correctly
* Move remaining celtix.bus stuff from celtix-api to celtix-rt
* Change ResourceResolver API to use generics for the resolve call
* Added flag to ConfigurationMetadataBuilder to turn off the processing/unmarshalling of default values.   JAXB classes are not always available at code generation time.
